MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 364c2b772391e46dba637935c558b9b2, type: 3}
  m_Name: Bat
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::MythSO
  pageNumber: 121
  mythName: Bat
  omens:
  - '1. A smug musician, drumming. He sings

    "the great winged one grows, and
    we are

    the feast" but he insists it''s just a song.'
  - '2. A flock of various birds, grounded. They

    look to be grovelling toward
    the darkest

    part of the sky. They scatter if disturbed.'
  - '3. A long table is laid out, commoners

    gathered for a feast. Every bowl
    is filled

    with worms, which people reluctantly eat

    by the handful.
    They say the Feast of

    Worms will deny the Bat its food.'
  - '4. Exhausted farmers gather pigs, cows, and

    sheep. They''re heading to
    a nearby lake

    for a great sacrifice, hoping the bloody

    water will sate
    the Bat''s wicked hunger.'
  - '5. A crowd are lighting fires outside a cave,

    the Bat hiding within. They
    aim to smoke

    it out. The Bat eventually emerges, and

    fights only enough
    to allow it to flee.'
  - '6. Wings broken, dragged in chains, the Bat

    is being taken to the Seat
    of Power to be

    judged for its long list of crimes against

    the Realm
    (see opposite).'
  verse: 'Spoil the loaf, taint the wine

    To starve a fiend is most divine'
  castEntries:
  - name: The Bat, Most Wicked of All Beasts
    statBlock: 'VIG 15, CLA 15, SPI 3, 7 GD

      A2 (huge body)'
    notes: 'Thrashing wings (d8 blast) or bite (2d10)

      Wants sweet fruit and
      a dark place to rest.'
  - name: Crowd of Bat Hunters, led by Radlef
    statBlock: 'VIG 10, CLA 7, SPI 13, 3 GD

      Weaponised tools (d8 long), Radlef
      has a'
    notes: 'Bow (d6 long) and batbane arrows (no effect)

      Certainty in their
      convictions.'
  - name: Travelling Musician, Keork
    statBlock: 'VIG 11, CLA 11, SPI 16, 4 GD

      Drum with red ribbons, dagger
      (d6)'
    notes: Enjoys hearing how badly others sing.
  flavorTable:
    title: CRIMES OF THE BAT
    columns:
    - header: Act
      values:
      - Mass murder
      - Devouring cattle
      - Spoiling crops
      - Spreading plague
      - Shortening Spring
      - Causing nightmares
    - header: Proof
      values:
      - A song
      - One eyewitness
      - Popular rumour
      - Proclaimed by Seer
      - Dubious confession
      - It's self-evident!
  visibleByDefault: 0
  visibleMarkerPrefab: {fileID: 0}
